{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"herculean-afeard-vulture","description":"## Why\nEpic AC7 specifies the enforcement merge-gate as `rebar verify-identity\n--require-authenticated --since <identity.enforce_since>` that (a) exits non-zero when any\nenforced event is not `certified`, (b) emits one structured report entry\n`{event_uuid, ticket_id, commit, author, verdict, display}` per non-certified event, (c)\n**grandfathers** pre-cutover events, and (d) runs as a CI merge-gate workflow. The delivered\ngate (3183 / change 580) meets the SPIRIT (`rebar verify-authorship`, opt-in via config,\nnon-zero exit, replay-never-rejects, fsck/show grouping) but not the LETTER: wrong command\nname, no `--require-authenticated`/`--since` flags, text-only output (no JSON report), no\n`enforce_since` grandfathering, and no CI workflow file. The epic completion-verifier flagged\nAC7 unmet. This story builds AC7 in full. (Remediation of epic gnu-whale-ichor; user chose\n\"build it\".)\n\n## What\nBuild the AC7 enforcement surface on top of the delivered merge-gate, in\n`src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py` (+ config + a report schema + a CI workflow):\n\n- **`rebar verify-identity` command.** Make `verify-identity` the canonical command name\n  (add it to the CLI intercept in `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py`), keeping `verify-authorship`\n  as a back-compat alias routing to the same `cli()`. Regenerate the CLI reference\n  (`docs/cli-reference.md`) + INTERCEPT_COMMANDS/_LADDER so the drift gate stays green.\n- **`--require-authenticated` flag.** Forces enforcement ON for the run regardless of\n  `identity.require_authenticated` config (the CI job passes it explicitly). Without it,\n  config governs (unchanged).\n- **`--since <ref>` grandfathering.** Default from a new `identity.enforce_since` config\n  key (env `REBAR_IDENTITY_ENFORCE_SINCE`). An event is ENFORCED iff its introducing commit\n  is `<ref>` or a descendant of `<ref>` (at/after cutover, via `git merge-base\n  --is-ancestor <ref> <event_commit>`); an event whose commit does NOT descend `<ref>` is\n  **grandfathered** â€” its verdict is still computed and reported, but it never fails the\n  gate. With no `--since`/`enforce_since`, all events are enforced (current behavior).\n- **`--format json` report.** Emit a JSON array of entries\n  `{event_uuid, ticket_id, commit, author, verdict, display}` â€” one per NON-`verified`\n  in-scope event (with a `grandfathered: bool`), validated against a new\n  `src/rebar/schemas/verify_identity_report.schema.json`. `display` is the grouping\n  (`verified`/`unverified`/`unsigned`); `verdict` is the raw verdict. Default output stays\n  the existing human text.\n- **CI merge-gate workflow.** Add `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` (or a gated step)\n  that runs `rebar verify-identity --require-authenticated --since <identity.enforce_since>`\n  over the merged log and fails the build on a non-zero exit.\n- Exit semantics: non-zero iff an ENFORCED (non-grandfathered) event is not `verified`\n  (`certified`), under `--require-authenticated` (or config). Grandfathered/advisory â†’ 0.\n\n## Scope\nIn: the `verify-identity` command name + alias, `--require-authenticated`/`--since` flags,\n`enforce_since` config + env, the JSON report + its schema, grandfathering by commit\nancestry, and the CI workflow. Out: the per-event classification itself (delivered +\nTS2/TS3, unchanged) and the schema verdict enum (AC10). Folds into the 3183 commit (change\n580); the CI workflow + report schema are new files in that commit.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar verify-identity --all` behaves as the merge-gate (same classification), and\n  `rebar verify-authorship --all` still works as an alias (test both dispatch).\n- [ ] `--require-authenticated` forces enforcement: with config off, `rebar verify-identity\n  --require-authenticated --all` still exits non-zero on an unsigned/non-verified enforced\n  event (test asserts exit code).\n- [ ] `--since <ref>` grandfathers pre-cutover events: with an unsigned event introduced\n  BEFORE the cutover ref and another AFTER, `--require-authenticated --since <ref>` fails\n  ONLY for the post-cutover one; the pre-cutover event is reported `grandfathered` and does\n  NOT fail the gate (test asserts exit code + that the pre-cutover event is grandfathered).\n- [ ] `--format json` emits an array of `{event_uuid, ticket_id, commit, author, verdict,\n  display, grandfathered}` entries for the non-verified events, validating against\n  `verify_identity_report.schema.json`; a test asserts an entry's field set + that `display`\n  is the grouping value and `verdict` the raw verdict.\n- [ ] A CI workflow file exists under `.github/workflows/` that invokes `rebar\n  verify-identity --require-authenticated --since <â€¦>` as a gating job (test/asserts the\n  file exists and references the command).\n- [ ] The CLI-reference drift gate passes (verify-identity documented; alias noted).\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py` (verify-identity name + --require-authenticated/--since flags + JSON report + grandfathering)\n- `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` (intercept verify-identity + alias verify-authorship)\n- `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` (identity.enforce_since + env REBAR_IDENTITY_ENFORCE_SINCE)\n- `src/rebar/schemas/verify_identity_report.schema.json` (new report schema)\n- `.github/workflows/verify-identity.yaml` (new CI merge-gate workflow)\n- `docs/cli-reference.md` (regenerated: verify-identity)","id":"bff8-5b30-731b-4715","parent_id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"identity: verify-identity enforcement CLI + --since grandfathering + JSON report + CI gate (epic AC7)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783901887573330001,"uuid":"95b19535-d024-4088-832f-ad7a9326a575"}